title: A Minakari Tray from Iran/Pakistan
creator: Mr. & Mrs. Louis Bailey Audigier
description: A tray made out of copper and enamel (Minakari), which is the art of ornamenting the surface of metal by opowdered glass. On this tray radiating description says "Allah", "Malik" and "Mohammad" ( partial).  The dot in the centre is skewd to onside, an intended imperfection signifying that only god is perfect
subject: Tray; Minamari; artifact

title: A Mughal Dynasty panel made of sandstone from Unknown Mughal Pavillion
creator: Ardath & Joel E. Rynning Acquisition funds
description: The Panel is on of the 2 facades of a grand but. unknown Mughal pavillion from Northern India. It depicts a Peacock (Which is currently the national bird of India) with a snake in its mouth. The large fanned tail that fills most of the cusped Arch is known as Mihrab- a niche in a wall that points towards Mecca, the direction in which Muslims pray.
subject: Object:  Panel: Mughal Dynasty: Norhtern India
